value.0: Czerka employees are detached from emotion for the most part. They generally care very little for their own company unless it benefits them personally, and are susceptible to completely abandoning their post should it endanger them. A Czerka Employee is only as loyal as their paycheque dictates. This employee looks at you in disproval before getting back to work; time is money!
This appears to be the uniform of a Czerka Corporation employee.

Bertha is an older woman of about fifty five. She looks at you with anger and a lack of patience, ready to scream at the slightest of infractions. She does her job fairly well, but complains often about incompetent employees. She is usually correct.

A good sauce pan is every cook's friend.  Both for boiling potatoes, and restoring order. Grab this pan, open one can of whoop-ass, and do lunch!
Standard issue beer mug. Sad looking when its empty, but still good in a pinch. And the design on the rim can make a good impression in a brawl.
